headline: CME's Q2 beat, Lamb Weston's cost savings, Cal-Maine's Q4 beat
summary: Yahoo Finance anchor Josh Lipton tracks today's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. CME Group (CME) reported second quarter earnings results that were better than analysts expected. Lamb Weston (LW) stock is surging after the company reported a fourth quarter earnings beat. The company also announced a cost-savings plan, hoping to save at least $250 million annually by the end of 2028. Cal-Maine Foods (CALM) stock is also surging after the company delivered better-than-expected fourth quarter results. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: CME beats profit estimates as volatility drives record trading quarter
summary: The company, which facilitates trading of futures and options, benefits during volatile periods, as seen with the onset of U.S. President Donald Trump's seesawing tariffs in early April.  The volatility index, which reflects the extent to which investors are snapping up protection against volatility, reached record levels in early April before retreating on expectations of trade deals.  Excluding one-time items, profit attributable to CME shareholders was $1.07 billion, or $2.96 per share, for the quarter ended June 30.
